# Environment Variables for Vercel Deployment

## Frontend (.env in root)
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_stripe_publishable_key_here

## Backend (Server Environment Variables)
MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string_here
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your_stripe_secret_key_here
PORT=5000

## Instructions for Vercel:
1. Go to your Vercel project settings
2. Navigate to "Environment Variables"
3. Add each variable above (except PORT, which Vercel handles automatically)
4. Make sure to add them for "Production", "Preview", and "Development" environments
5. Redeploy after adding the variables

## Note:
- The backend (server) should be deployed separately (e.g., on Render, Railway, or Vercel Serverless Functions)
- Update the API URLs in the frontend code to point to your deployed backend URL
